FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Labuschagne! The man in the deep tried to stop this one but he failed! Flatter on middle, Marnus flicks this one through the square leg region and the ball touches the ropes, as the fielder tried to stop it.

FOUR! Marnus sends one to the ropes now! Uses the crease well on this occasion. Ashwin, again goes for a short delivery around off, Labuschagne goes back deep in his crease and slaps this one through the cover region again and the ball speeds away to the ropes.
Short and around off, WP punches this one to the cover region and rotates the strike.
Flatter and on middle, tucked to the leg side. No run is the call by Will.
On off, blocked out.
Length ball on off, Marnus defends it out.
Back of a length on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Pucovski flicks it through square leg for a single.
Back of a length on off, Will defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Pucovski looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. A tame appeal by the players but no says the umpire. Looked to be way too high.
Floated delivery on middle, Labuschagne sweeps it to square leg.
On middle, Marnus flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Pucovski flicks it towards fine leg for a run.
On middle, Labuschagne flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards the leg side.

NOT OUT! Pucovski survives! It looks like Pant did not take a clean catch, after all. The third umpire thinks he has enough evidence to suggest that Rishabh did not take a clean catch. Siraj bangs in a short ball on middle, Pucovski goes for the pull shot but he is only able to glove this one and the ball lobs over Pant. He turns around, runs a little and then takes it, but the ball pops out. He has a second attempt at this and seems to have taken it. The umpire's take this upstairs and want to have a look at this, which is then deemed to have dropped on the ground before he caught it on the second attempt. Will be not out.
The umpires are checking if Pant has taken a clean catch. The third umpire wants to confirm. Looks like he hasn't.
On off, tapped to cover-point. Pucovski first thinks about exchanging ends but then raises his blade and lets Marnus know that the single is not possible now.
Angles in a good length delivery on off, Will punches this to the cover region.
Bumper on middle, WP knows what he has to do. Sits under this one.
On off, kept out solidly. Pucovski is at 32 runs off 76 balls. A good, solid start to his Test career so far for the debutant.
Length delivery around the off pole, Marnus looks to block this one out but the ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes through the point region. One run.
Floats it nicely around off, Pucovski blocks this one out as well. Six runs off this over.
On off, WP pushes it back to the bowler.
Two, this time. Flatter again and outside off, Will rocks on his back foot and punches this one through the point region to pick up a couple of runs.
On off, blocked.

FOUR! Good footwork by Will and he bags a boundary! Also, brings up 50 runs for the Aussies. Short and outside off, Pucovski makes some room and slaps this one through the cover region, past the diving fielder there and into the ropes.
Floated on middle, Will tucks it to the square leg region.
Back of a length on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Full on middle, Marnus flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Down the leg side, Labuschagne looks to flick but misses it.
Back of a length on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.

DROPPED! Pant is the culprit here. He should have taken it and the debutant is handed another life. Tossed up on off, Pucovski looks to defend but gets a slight outside edge. It goes towards the keeper where Pant tries to take with one hand but spills it. Rishabh will be disappointed with this one.
Full on off, Pucovski drives it through covers for a couple.
Flighted delivery on middle, Pucovski flicks it towards the leg side.
Loopy delivery on off, Will punches it to covers.
Floated ball on off, Pucovski keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Pucovski flicks it to square leg.

DRINKS. Time for a refreshment. The Aussies will be very happy with how Labuschagne and Pucovski have dealt with the Indian bowling ever since the resumption of play. They have added some good runs to the board and are close to the 50-run mark now as well. India, on the other hand, have bowled testing lines and lengths but they have not been able to grab another wicket, since Warner fell. Some more wickets is what they will be thinking of before the Tea break.
Short delivery on middle, Labuschagne pulls it to sqaure leg, where Jadeja makes a good stop.
Back of a length on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery on middle, Marnus blocks it off the back foot.
Full again on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, Pucovski flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length on off, Pucovski defends it off the back foot.
Mohammed Siraj is back on. 6-1-23-1 are his numbers so far. Looks like Rahane is going to make Saini wait slightly more, before handing him the ball.
Floated delivery on off, Marnus keeps it out. A maiden over from Ashwin.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to short fine leg.
On off, Labuschagne blocks it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Short and outside off, Marnus looks to cut but misses it.
Flighted ball on off, Labuschagne offers a solid defense on this one.

Tossed up delivery on off, Labuschagne skips down the track and works this to the cover region. Thinks about the single, comes a few paces down the deck, but then decides otherwise and sends Will back.
Length delivery on off, Pucovski defends it out towards the mid on region. Maiden by Bumrah.
Back of a length on off, Pucovski punches it to covers. A good punch by Will but it was straight to the fielder.
Bouncer on middle, Pucovski does well to duck under it.
Length delivery on off, Will blocks it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Pucovski defends it off the back foot. Quick, early call again by Pucovski to say no to the single.
Good length delivery on off, Pucovski defends it off the back foot towards point. Good communication by Will as he is quick to deny the single, whenever he feels there isn't one on offer.
Tossed up delivery on off, Labuschagne offers a solid defense on this one.
On middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Just a gentle push, this. Full delivery on off, Labuschagne pushes it through covers for a couple.
Floated delivery on middle, Marnus defends it off the back foot.
Flighted ball on off, Labuschagne punches it to covers.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards the leg side.
Length ball on middle, Pucovski flicks it to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Pucovski looks to push but misses it due to the extra bounce on this one.
Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Length ball on off, Marnus offers a solid defense to this one.
Back of a length on off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
Good length delivery on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
On off again, Pucovski keeps it out.
On off, worked to the off side.
Flatter and around off, WP defends this one out off his back foot, back towards Ashwin.
Short again and outside off, Pucovski punches this one through the cover region and picks up a brace.
Short and around off, spins back in, Will pushes this to the leg side off his back foot.
Flatter and on middle, clipped to the leg side.

FOUR! Well played by Marnus! He sends this one past the ropes! On a fuller length around off, Labuschagne punches this one through the mid on region, where the fielder dives, but is not able to stop the ball, which then runs past the ropes.
Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN. Lovely bowling by Jasprit. Again, he goes to bowl a good length just around off, ML looks to block this one out but the ball takes the outside edge and goes into Pant's mitts.

EDGED...SHORT! Ohhh..great bowling by Bumrah! He almost gets the big wicket of Marnus but the ball falls short of the fielder there. On a good length around off, Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards Pujara, at first slip, but the ball falls short.
Goes to bowl a good length delivery outside off this time, Labuschagne plays this to the cover region.
Slightly behind the good length area and around off, ML pushes this to the leg side.
Flighted and on middle, pushed to the mid on region. Just the single off Ashwin's first over.
Loopy and on middle, Marnus skips down the track and works it through mid-wicket for a single.
On off, blocked out.
Floated on middle, flicked to the square leg region.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Flatter and on middle, ML keeps it out. 'Come on Ash, come on Ash', is the call from Pant, behind the stumps.
Ravichandran Ashwin is into the attack.
Bouncer outside off, WP sways away and lets it go.

Quick single this time. Angles in a good length ball around off, Labuschagne taps this one to the off side and scampers for the single. Will responds and runs in. Bumrah runs in and has a shy at the striker's end but he misses.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Goes fuller and on middle this time, flicked away to the mid-wicket region for a single. Will moves to 21 from 45 balls with this single.
On a length and around the off pole, Pucovski punches this one with a straight blade to the mid on region.
Angled in from around off, kept out by Will. He denies the single on this occasion.
On off, Labuschagne is solid in his defense.
On off, kept out to the leg side.
Good length on off, blocked out by Marnus. 'NO RUNNNNN', says Marnus, in regard to the single.

Very nice shot to collect three runs. Siraj bowls in a back of a length ball around off, Will hops and tucks this one through the mid-wicket region and Ashwin gives it a chase and pulls it back before the ropes. Saves one run for his side.
Length delivery around the off pole, WP pushes it back towards Siraj, who catches this one on his followthrough.
On off, pushed to the short mid on fielder.
Quicker and shorter on middle, ML sits under this one.

FOUR. Good shot. Marnus takes the ball on this time and he dispatches this one to the ropes. This one is shorter in length and on middle, Labuschagne swivel-pulls this one to the deep square leg region to find the ropes.
Another length delivery outside off, Marnus lets this one through in typical Marnus Labuschagne fashion. Swings his bat in the followthrough.
Outside off, shorter in length, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
On off, ML looks to block but the ball takes the inside edge and hits the pads.
Short of a length this time, around off, it nips back in after pitching, Marnus does really well in leaving this one alone.
Short again, down the leg side, WP just lets this one through to the keeper. A maiden by Siraj.
Shorter and on the body, Pucovski fends this one to the short fine leg region.
Siraj, this time, drags his length back and bowls a shorter one around off, Will sways away from the line of the ball.
Another length ball on off, Pucovski fends this one out.
On off, blocked out.
Length ball on off, Pucovski defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
Outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Full delivery on off, Marnus defends it to mid off.
Length ball outside off, Marnus offers no shot to this one.
Length delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket. The fielder there, dives to his right and makes a good stop.
Good length ball outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Pucovski defends it off the front foot.
Similar ball as the last delivery, this time it is Marnus, he punches this one through the mid off region and the fielder gives it chase and stops it before the ropes. The batters collect three runs.
Confident push by Will. Gets three runs on this occasion. On a length and around off, Pucovski punches this one through the mid off region and will collect three runs.
An appeal for LBW but turned down. A back of a length ball around middle and leg, Will looks to tuck it away but misses to get hit high on the pads. An appeal but no says the umpire.
On a good length around off, Will pushes this to the cover region.
We are back for resumption. The Indian players are out in the middle. Will Pucovski and Marnus Labuschagne will resume their batting for Australia. Mohammed Siraj will finish his over.

UPDATE 1450 local (0350 GMT) - Finally, the best news that we could hope for! PLAY WILL RESUME AT 1500 local (0400 GMT). The Indian players are slowly trotting out and are looking to warm up before the resumption of play as well. Tea will be taken at 1640 local (0540 GMT) and stumps are scheduled at 1830 local (0730 GMT) with 30 minutes extra permitted to make sure that the minimum overs are bowled.

UPDATE 1440 local (0340 GMT) - There seems to be an issue with the areas next to the pitch and the umpires are concerned about the same. The groundstaff are hard at work and are doing all they can to dry that area. The good news is that the sun is shining brightly. Stay tuned for further updates.

UPDATE 1420 local (0320 GMT) - Some more good news coming our way. It looks like all the covers have been taken off. An inspection is due 10 minutes from now. Hopefully, some cricket is just around the corner.

UPDATE 1409 local (0309 GMT) - Alright, some movement by the groundstaff as the covers are being taken off. The rain seems to have stopped for now. Let's hope that the rain does not pay another visit.
UPDATE 1355 local (0255 GMT) - It is still raining heavily and we need to wait longer for the game to resume. Fingers crossed. Stay tuned for the updates.

UPDATE 1334 local (0234 GMT) - Another bout of bad news coming our way. The umpires were supposed to inspect the field right now but it seems that the rain has not had it's final say and has returned. The covers are back on as well. All we can do is hope now.

UPDATE 1312 local (0212 GMT) - Well, finally some good news as it seems that the covers are coming back off. There is no confirmation as to what the start time would be but the rain seems to have stopped, which is a positive sign. The scheduled close of play now will be at 1830 local (0730 GMT) with 30 minutes extra so as to ensure that the minimum overs are bowled. Right, the news coming out is that the umpires will inspect the field at 1330 local (0230 GMT). Fingers crossed!

UPDATE 1300 local (0200 GMT) - Nothing new to update as it is still raining in Sydney. It seems that we will be in for a long delay as it looks to be heavy. Let's hope that we get some cricket on Day 1.

After winning the toss, Tim Paine decided that they were going to bat first. They had new openers for this Test as Warner and Pucovski walked out into the middle. Warner was showing some good intent and Will was looking solid out there, on his Test debut. But Siraj had other plans when he dangled a bait to Warner and David took it and lost his wicket in the process. Labuschagne walked out and with just 7.1 overs on the board, rain decided to play spoilsport and brought the first session to an early close. Hopefully, we see some cricket after the Lunch break.

UPDATE 1220 local (0120 GMT) - Well, early Lunch was on the cards and it has been taken now as the rain has been pretty persistent. It just seems to be that kind of a day. Let's hope that we have clear skies after the Lunch break.

UPDATE 1200 local (0100 GMT) - There are 30 minutes remaining for the scheduled Lunch break but the rain has gotten heavier. Early lunch is on the cards. But stick around for the official confirmation.

UPDATE 1145 local (0045 GMT) - Well, we hate to be the bearers of bad news but play should have been underway now. It seems that the rain has decided to pay yet another visit and the covers come back on. Sigh! Guess we'll just have to play the waiting game.

UPDATE 1133 local (0033 GMT) - Good news coming our way! It seems that the covers are coming off now. Let's hope that the rain does not decide to pay another visit and play can get underway shortly. We are getting an update that play will resume at 1145 local (0045 GMT). Also, the scheduled close of play will be extended to 1810 local (0710 GMT). No overs have been lost so far, provided the rain stays away.

UPDATE 1123 local (0023 GMT) - Well, good news as the covers seem to be coming off. Oh wait...Scratch that last update. The rain has started to pour down again and the covers come back on. Ahh..slightly frustating but rain was predicted on Day 1 and it could well be a start-stop sort of day.

UPDATE 1105 local (0005 GMT) - Seems that the rain has got slightly heavier and so the umpires have asked the players to go back and the covers are also on at the moment. The players walk off and the rain does not look too heavy and it should be just a short delay. Let's hope that it is just a passing shower.
A back of a length ball on middle, worked to the leg side.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket for a single.
A full ball on off, Will drives this one to the mid on region.
Short and around off, Will dabs this one away to the point region. Bumrah needs to try some more short balls when he is bowling to Pucovski.
On off, Pucovski pushes this towards point.
On middle, Will flicks it through the square leg region and picks up a couple.
Back of a length delivery and around off, WP hops and keeps it out well.
Outside off, Labuschagne lets it go.
Full delivery on middle, Pucovski drives it through mid on. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
FOUR! First boundary of the innings! Short of a length delivery on middle, Pucovski looks to pull but gets a top edge. It goes towards fine leg for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Pucovski defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length down the leg side, Pucovski looks to flick but misses it.
Length delivery on middle, Pucovski flicks it towards the leg side.
Good length delivery outside off, Marnus does not bother to play at that.
Outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Back of a length on middle, Pucovski flicks it through mid-wicket. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Length delivery on off, Will keeps it out.
Back of a length on off, Pucovski offers a solid defense on this one.
Length delivery on off, Pucovski defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery! Good length delivery outside off, Marnus looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Length ball outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get two runs.
Marnus Labuschagne is the new batsman in.

OUT! EDGED AND CAUGHT! India draw first blood! Warner's comeback does not end on a happy note for the left-hander and for the Aussies! Siraj, again, continues his good form in this Test series and he breaks this new opening stand. Siraj dishes this on a length around off, it moves away after pitching, Warner is drawn into the shot and he swings his blade at this. He can only induce an outside edge and the ball flies towards the slip cordon. Pujara is the man there at first slip and he is not going to drop this.
BEATEN! Back of a length outside off, Warner looks to swing at it but misses it.
Length delivery on off, Warner defends it to point.
Good length on off, WP pushes this to the off side to complete the over.
On off, again, Will pushes this one back towards Jasprit.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length and around off, David pushes this to the cover region and picks up a single.
On off, blocked to the off side.
Quick run. On off, Warner taps this to the off side and runs across for a quick single.
Pucovski is up and running! His first runs in Test cricket. Length on middle and leg, Will flicks this one to the fine leg region to pick up a run.
Down the leg side, Will looks to flick this one but he misses his shot.
Length and on off, Will is solid in his defense.
Length again, this time, and on middle and leg, David clips this one to the fine leg region for a single.
Warner and Australia open their account in this game! On a length outside off, Warner punches this one through the cover-point region to pick up a brace.
Mohammed Siraj to bowl from the other end.
On off, well kept out. A steady start by Bumrah and also a maiden to start off.
SWING AND A MISS! Bumrah, this time, drags his length back and bowls it on a shorter length on middle, Will looks to pull but misses. A tame appeal by Pant for caught behind but no says the umpire.
Outside off again, on a length, Will watchfully let this one through to Pant.
Another length delivery outside off, Will shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on off, Pucovski blocks this one out.
Some movement noticed early up. Bumrah goes for a length delivery outside off, moves away after taking the deck, Will has no issues in leaving this one alone.

Right then! We are done with all the pre-match formalities as the action for the 'Pink Test' is all set to begin. The players of India are in a huddle and Ajinkya Rahane is imparting some final words of wisdom before the players spread out on the field. The openers of Australia, David Warner and Will Pucovski stride out into the middle. A change in the openers for the hosts and it will be interesting to see how they fare. Jasprit Bumrah to speed in. Pucovski to face. Here he comes...
The players are out in the middle and are standing in respect of their respective National Anthems. First, it will be India's National Anthem, followed by Australia's.

PITCH REPORT - Glenn McGrath says that there is a slight tinge of grass but it still should be a very good surface to bat on. Goes onto say that there could be a lot of runs on offer. Also adds that both the captains would look to bat first.

Australia (Playing XI) - David Warner (IN PLACE OF JOE BURNS), Will Pucovski (IN PLACE OF TRAVIS HEAD), Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Matthew Wade, Cameron Green, Tim Paine (C/WK), Pat Cummins, Mitchell Starc, Nathan Lyon, Josh Hazlewood.

India (Playing XI) - Rohit Sharma (IN PLACE OF MAYANK AGARWAL), Shubman Gill, Cheteshwar Pujara, Ajinkya Rahane (C), Hanuma Vihari, Rishabh Pant (WK), Ravindra Jadeja, Ravichandran Ashwin, Jasprit Bumrah, Mohammed Siraj, Navdeep Saini (IN PLACE OF UMESH YADAV).

Ajinkya Rahane, the skipper of India, starts off by saying that he is happy that Rohit Sharma is back and he has looked good in the nets. Feels that he is happy for Saini and that he has been good in domestic cricket. Feels that they are just focusing on this Test match and it is all about giving your best out there.

The captain of Australia, Tim Paine, starts off by saying that they discussed in areas that they need to improve. Says that Warner is back and Pucovski is making their debut and they are excited. Feels that they will try and play their best cricket in Sydney and they'll go about their business in this Test. States that Travis Head misses out and that he has not done a lot wrong but they had to shuffle things around.
TOSS - The men who matter, Tim Paine and Ajinkya Rahane are out in the middle for the all important toss. Up goes the coin and it lands in Australia's favour. THEY WILL BAT FIRST!

Another interesting Day of Test cricket is what this is building up to be. Which team looks to take the day? Will the hosts start this day and take control or will India make another statement and push the Kangaroos on the back foot? A lot will depend on the toss as well. So join us as we bring you the toss and all the relevant updates...

India, on the other hand, will be in high spirits heading into this game. Their last victory will not be something that they will forget so easily. Without Kohli, Ishant, Rohit, Bhuvneshwar and also Umesh Yadav, they won the last game very solidly and they proved everyone who doubted them wrong. With the same mindset and form, they can take a huge leap in this game by winning and taking a 2-1 lead, with the final Test to go. Just like Australia, they have also received a boost as Rohit Sharma has been included in the Playing XI and a Test debut is also being handed to Navdeep Saini.

A wounded lion is more dangerous than a hungry one. This is the definition of the Australian team right now. They proved their talents in the first Test and bundled this Indian side to a humbling defeat, but in the next game, they were outplayed all over the field and they let India come back in the series, to make it level and that would have hurt them. Losing a Test match at home would have hurt them and that is why a comprehensive show is what they will be hoping for and their attempts to do this were boosted as their star opener, David Warner is back into the squad and this is something that they desperately needed. Steven Smith has not fared well so far and the Kangaroos will be hoping for him to fire.

Two Tests done. Series level at 1-1. Talking about the series so far, A humiliation dished to India by Australia in the first Test and without the able aid of Virat Kohli, Rahane has shown his mettle and his leadership skills as he has led this Indian side to a memorable victory in the second Test of the series to get them level. And now the third Test looms upon us.

We are back for the final session of Day 3. The Indian players are out in the middle. David Warner and Will Pucovski will open the innings for Australia. Jasprit Bumrah will start the proceedings for India. Pant, who got injured while batting has gone for scans, thus Wriddhiman Saha is keeping wickets for India.
... Day 3, Session 3 ...

Right! Australia have got a substantial lead of 94. The final and long session coming your way. How will the Aussie openers go about it. Will the Indians be able to strike early and dent Australia early? We will find out all these answers in a short while.

The Aussies were just brilliant with the ball in this session. In spite of that 50-run stand between Pujara and Pant, they persisted with their short bowling. It paid off and they prized out a few wickets with that line. Their fielding was superb as they got 3 run outs. Cummins was the star for them as he got a 4-fer in this innings. Hazlewood and Lyon too kept things really tight. Lyon didn't get a wicket but was superb in his spell.

The session started with Pujara and Pant doing well to score a few runs. Pant then got hit one on his left arm and started feeling uncomfortable. He was peppered with a few short balls. He was eventually prized out by Hazlewood. Pujara continued his blockathon and got to his half ton but was soon removed by a Cummins. Indians then lost two more in the form of run outs as Ashwin threw his wicket away, responding very slowly for a single. A few blows from Jadeja towards the end meant that India managed to bring the deficit under 100.

A terrific phase of play for Australia and they have just rattled the Indians have taken a huge lead here. Just brilliant by them to roll over the Indians and take a big lead of 120. Not good from India though. Three run outs in the innings in a Test match is absolutely a timid effort from the Indians. Also, it is TEA time on Day 3.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! There is a spike as the ball gets closer to the bat, as shown by the Snicko. After banging three short, Cummins bowls a length ball just outside off, Siraj pokes at it without moving his feet. He ends up nicking it behind and the Aussies celebrate.The finger goes up but Siraj signals the 'T'. Replays roll in and they show a big spike on the Snicko. So, the onfield call will stay. India are bowled out for 244.
Siraj has been given out caught behind. He goes for the review straightaway. Let's see if there is any wood.
Cummins bangs it short again. Siraj ducks well again. Three more balls for him to survive. Will Cummins dish out a fuller one now?
Banged short and just outside off, Siraj backs away and then tries to poke at it. Misses.
A bouncer just around off, Siraj ducks under it. In fact he was down before Cummins released the ball.
Pat Cummins is back again.

FOUR! Slammed away. Shortish around off, Jadeja pulls this one behind square and finds the gap at deep square leg area. Gets a boundary on the last ball of the over, which means Siraj will be on strike the next over.

Shortish around middle, Jadeja plays it towards mid-wicket. Siraj at the non-striker's end looks to steal the run, but is sent back. The fielder has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses. Had that hit, Siraj was a goner.
Shortish on middle, Jadeja hops and somehow manages to keep it down.
Play and a miss! A length ball outside off, Jadeja goes for the slash but misses the ball altogether.
Shorter around middle and off, Jadeja lets it be.

Length outside off, Jadeja throws his hands at it and the ball races away fine towards third man area. The fielder there does well to stop the ball and throws it back. Jadeja refuses to take the single.
A single and Jadeja will keep the strike. Banged short and outside off, Jadeja stays back and guides it over the slip cordon. The third man fielder makes a diving stop to his right.

Dropped? Yes. But that was a hit really hard chance. A length ball on middle and leg, Jadeja flicks it uppishly. Labuschagne at short leg responds quickly and throws his right hand. The ball hits his palm but goes out.

Jadeja in some sort of trouble. Looks like he was hit on his thumb on the last ball. The Indian physio walks out as Jadeja gets some attention. He is getting his some taping around his thumb. He is struggling to get the gloves around his hand. But he is a tough character. He is ready now.
Back of a length and on middle, kept out.
Two more! Fuller and outside off, Jadeja strokes it through covers and scampers back for a couple. The lead is under 100 now.

IN THE AIR ..AND SAFE!! A length on middle, Jadeja again goes for the slog, gets the top edge this time again behind the keeper. The fielder from third man tries to catch the ball but the ball lands short of him and Jadeja takes a quick couple of runs before the fielder returns the ball back to Paine. Useful runs these for India.

FOUR! Enough of ducking says Jadeja. A short ball on middle, Jadeja goes for the pull, gets a top edge which runs away towards the boundary at fine leg area. It bounces well ahead of the ropes but nonetheless a boundary for Jadeja.
Bangs it short and it goes well over Siraj. The last ball at the no. 11 is a wasted one from Green.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and wide outside off, Siraj cuts it through backward point and finds the fence.
Siraj is underway! Fuller and around middle, he pushes it through mid on and gets a brace.
Another bouncer! Goes over the ducking batter.
Pitched up and outside off, Siraj looks to drive but misses.
And he bangs it short first up. Siraj ducks under it.
Will Paine go for one of his quicks to rattle the no. 11? Yes. Not as express as Starc but here's Cameron Green again.
A bouncer outside off. Jadeja cannot do much about it as he watches it go behind. Siraj will be on strike for the next over.

EDGED AND FOUR! Welcome runs! Fuller and outside off, Jadeja goes for a big slog again. The ball though takes the bottom edge and goes behind. Paine dives to his right and tries to stop but the ball evades him and goes to the fence.
FOUR! Useful boundary. Full and around off, Jadeja nails it through mid on for a boundary. Starc has overstepped too.
Shortish and around middle, Jadeja goes for the pull but this one keeps low and Jadeja misses. An appeal from behind the wickets from Paine but turned down.
Mohammed Siraj is the last man in for India.

OUT! RUN OUT! 3rd run out of the innings. Jadeja clips this fuller ball towards deep square leg and immediately calls for two. The fielder from short leg, Labuschagne chases the ball down and scores a direct hit at the non-striker's end. Third umpire has been called for and replays show that Bumrah is well short there and has to make his way back to the pavilion. Australia have been excellent in the field especially with the direct hits. India 9 down now.
Direct hit again! Looks like Bumrah is a gonner this time. Yes. he is. He is gone by a big margin.
Short again this time on leg, Jadeja thinks for the pull but ducks under it.
Short and angling away from Jadeja, he lets it be.
Tossed up around off. Bumrah prods forwards and blocks this one.
Floated on middle, Jadeja turnes this one towards deep mid-wicket and takes a run.  Bumrah thinks for a second, but Jadeja sends him back.
Flatter around off, played towards short third man.
Fuller on middle, Jadeja blocks this out.
Tossed up and around off, pushed towards cover.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and just outside off, Jadeja cuts it through backward point and it races away to the fence.
And he too gets welcomed with a bumper. Does well to get down.
Jasprit Bumrah is in next.

OUT! TAKEN! Starc gets the wicket with that short ball tactics. Smart from Paine to bring him back. Not that smart from Jadeja to expose Saini for entire six balls against Starc. Another short ball around off and middle, Saini is hopping to fend it away. This time the Aussies brought a man at silly point. The ball hits the upper part of the bat and it goes to Wade. Wade is not dropping this. Perfectly planned wicket.
Another short ball. Saini somehow manages to fend it off on the off side. Could've gone in the hands but Saini survives. Starc smiles.
Sharp bouncer! Saini looks to defend but it lobs up off the handle towards the off side.
Length ball around off, he punches it through covers and takes two.
Runs in and bangs it short but this is down the leg side.
Tailenders are in and Paine calls Starc to clean it up.
Flat and around off, poked to mid off for a single.
Full this time and he hits it nicely but straight to Lyon.
Around off, turning in from a shortish length, Saini goes deep in his crease and bunts it onto the pitch on the leg side. Looking solid in defense.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Flat and around off, pushed towards cover.
Floated around off, Saini comes on the front foot to block.
In the channel outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.

First runs for Saini in Test match cricket. Well, not really. Given leg byes. Fuller and on the pads, Saini looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes towards short fine leg and they take a leg run. Looked like there was some bat but no. Given leg byes.
And he is welcomed with a sharp bumper. Saini sits under it.
Navdeep Saini, the debutant, is the new man in.

OUT! RUN OUT! Ashwin is short. Poor, poor running from him. A fullish ball outside off, Jadeja drives this to the left of fielder at mid off and takes off for the run. Ashwin is slow to react to it. Cummins from mid off throws the ball to Marnus Labuschagne at the striker's end and he whips off the bails before Ashwin can make his ground. Third umpire has been called and the replays show Ashwin short by some margin. Waste of a wicket this by Ashwin. Second run out of the innings this. India 7 down now.
Is Ashwin short? Looks like he is short. Let's see the replays. Yes. He is a gonner.
Cameron Green is back on.
Length ball in the channel outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Tossed up and around off, Ashwin is on the front foot to block.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards point.
Flatter and around off, Ashwin stays back to defend.
On middle, turned towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Nicely played. a tossed up ball outside off, Ashwin comes down and drills this one down the ground past mid off for his second boundary.
Nathan Lyon is back.
Floated around off, Ashwin blocks this out.
Length around middle, Jadeja defends this one towards mid on. A maiden to start from Cummins after the break.
Short again on the body, Jadeja watches it closely and sways away from it.
Fullish ball around middle, Jadeja flicks this one towards mid-wicket and yells a loud 'NO'.
A bouncer now on middle and leg, Jadeja sits under this one.
Length ball around middle, Jadeja plays it softly towards point and takes off for a run, but returns back as Ashwin says 'NO'.
Fullish ball on off, Jadeja does well to block this out.

DRINKS! What an interesting hour this for Australia after Lunch. They took the new ball straightaway and got the rewards in the form of the wickets of both the set batters, Pant and Pujara. India are still 136 behind and the last recognized batting pair is at the crease. Interesting play coming up after this.
Good from Ashwin. A shortish ball around middle, he clips it behind square on the leg side for two.
A short leg placed straightaway.
And it is the bouncer from Josh. Ashwin somehow manages to keep it down.
FOUR! Ashwin is off the mark in style. A fuller ball outside off, Ashwin leans into the stroke and drives it through the covers. Fine shot to bring 200 up.
Banged short and on middle and leg, Ashwin ducks.
Fuller and around off, driven to mid off.
Misfield and a single. Jadeja is away. Fuller and around off, it is pushed straight to Starc at covers. He fumbles and Jadeja sneaks a run.
Good length and around middle, kept out. End of a successful over from Cummins.
Fullish and just outside off, poked towards gully. Ashwin wants a single but Green makes a diving stop. Ashwin returns as Green has a shy at the striker's end. He hits but Ashwin was back.
Beaten! This is brilliant from Cummins. Ashwin is beaten all ends up. A length ball just around off, Ashwin pokes at it but the ball goes away ever so slightly and goes past the outside edge.
A bouncer to welcome Ashwin. He sits under it.
Ravichandran Ashwin now comes in to partner Jadeja.

OUT! GONE! Huge wicket. Cummins is the man who has done it again. Big, big wicket. Excellent from Cummins. Good length and around off, it shoots off a touch after pitching. Pujara is glued in his crease as he pokes at it. The ball takes the gloves and goes behind. Paine is not going to miss out. A simple catch for him and he gobbles it. The battling knock from Pujara comes to an end and that leaves India in a massive trouble. They are still 143 behind.
Back of a length and down the leg side. Left alone.
Fuller ball around off, Jadeja prods forward and defends this out.
A short ball to welcome Jadeja at the crease. Jadeja lets it go through. Stares exchanged and in the end, smiles.
Who will come out now ? Ravindra Jadeja is in now at number 7.

OUT! TAKEN! Pant's stay has been cut short. Hazlewood is the man who strikes. A fuller ball outside off, Pant without any feet movement goes for the drive but ends up getting an outside edge. The ball goes to Warner at first slip. It goes quickly to him but he reacts sharply and holds onto it. Great take from the southpaw. Not from the one with the bat though as it was way outside off and he could've had easily left it alone. A start thrown away again by Pant.
Fuller around off, Pant pushes this one towards covers.

FIFTY FOR PUJARA! This has been one fighting knock from him. Maybe he has been a little too cautious but that's how he bats and goes about the business. He tires the opposition down and then starts scoring. That's exactly how he has done here. He hit his first boundary of the innings after playing 100 balls. And after that, it hasn't been that difficult for him. He gets to the milestone by flicking the fuller ball around off towards mid-wicket for one. This is his 26th in Tests and slowest of his career.
Shortish around middle, Pant hops and defends this one on the leg side uncomfortably but runs a quick run to give Pujara the strike.
A bumper coming in with the angle, Pujara sways away slighlty and evades the ball.
Length on middle, Pujara plays it towards mid-wicket.
On a length around middle, Pujara clips this one towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! Nicely done from Pujara. A fuller ball just outside off, he comes on the front foot and then opens the bat face. It goes between second slip and gully. It races away to the fence. He moves to 49. The boundary brings up 50-run stand between the two. A valuable stand.
Ouch! Short ball on the body. Pujara looks to duck but gets hit flush on his left shoulder.
In the channel outside off, Pujara leaves that one.
Another solid defense from Pant as Josh bowls it around off on a length.
Around off on a good length, Pant blocks.
Pant moves on the leg side and takes a breather again. Clearly not comfortable.
Fullish and just outside off, driven to mid off.
Shortish and around off and middle, Pant blocks off his toes.
This time he lets it go to the keeper.
Beaten! Length ball outside off, Pant looks to drive away from his body. Only to get beaten.
It is the short ball but Pant is pant. He goes hard at it and pulls it nicely. The deep square leg fielder does well to stop. A single taken.

The Indian physio is out in the middle, assisting Pant. A slight halt in play as the physio checks the elbow. Pant is clearly in pain but he is a tough guy. He is getting his arm taped. He is trying to feel the bat but is not looking comfortable. He is a tough character though and he gets ready now. What will be the follow-up ball from Cummins?

Short and around off, Pant look to pull but misses to get hit on the arm. Pant is looking in some pain here. No elbow guard and he is hit flush on his left elbow. Didn't bounce as much as Pant expected it to be.
This one is angled in from a length on middle, Pant looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad.
Play and a miss! A fuller ball just outside off, Pant looks to drive on the up but the ball beats his outside edge.
Very full and around off, digged out to mid on.
Length ball around off, Pant is on the front foot to block.
Pat Cummins is back on. His numbers are 17-8-24-2 so far.
Short and just outside off, Pujara sways away.
Good length and around off, Pujara is solid in defense.
Fuller and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Good length and around off, kept out.

Pujara is beaten again. A superb ball from Josh. This is just outside off, Pujara looks to defend but is beaten as the ball first comes in and then straightens. Didn't go chasing and hence no edge there.
Fuller and outside off, stroked through cover-point for one.
Beaten! Lovely ball to end the over. Shortish and around middle and off, angling away. Pujara pokes at it. Only to get beaten.
Length ball around off and middle, pushed to mid on.
A bumper on middle and leg, Pujara sits under it.
Shortish and around off, poked towards point.
Starc pitches it up and it was just outside off, Pujara wanted to have a go at it but controlled his emotions and pulled his bat away. Good leave because it was angled away.
Wayward. This is way outside off on a good length. Pujara lets it go.
Another one in the channel outside off, Pant offers no shot again.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Squirts it away! Shortish and just outside off, Pant goes on the back foot and looks to cut. Ends up chopping it through gully for a boundary.
Fuller and around middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and around off, driven well but straight to the cover fielder.
Length ball around off, Pant looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes to mid-wicket.
Will Lyon continue from the other end? No way! The ball is new and it is Josh Hazlewood who is partnering Starc from the other end.
Outside off again, left alone.
Length ball outside off, Pujara shoulders arms.
Full again, pushed to mid on.
Short and down the leg side, Pujara lets it be.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Two for Pujara. A fuller ball around middle and leg, swinging in, Pujara flicks it through square leg for a brace.
Second new ball is due now! Will the Aussies go for it straightaway? Yes. They have taken the second new ball. Mitchell Starc will use it first up.
Floated around off, tucked away towards square leg for a run to keep strike. 1 run from Lyon's first over after Lunch.
On middle, played towards mid-wicket by Pujara.
Full and on middle, flicked to square leg.
Flat and around off, Pujara stays back to block.
Fuller anound middle, kept out.
Floated outside off, Pujara pads it away.

We are back for the afternoon session! The Aussie players stride out in the middle and the two Indian batters Cheteshwar Pujara and Rishabh Pant follow them. Nathan Lyon to start after Lunch. Second new ball will be available after 1 over. Here we go..
... DAY 3, SESSION 2 ...

So, the second session of the day promises to be another cracking one as the Indians look to build on with Pujara and Pant. The Aussies are just 1 over away from having the option of getting the second new ball and they will look to dictate terms with that. Join us for the second session in a short while.

Credit to the Aussie bowlers for keeping things really tight. Cummins and Starc made sure the runs were dried up in the first hour. Cummins got the reward when he got better of Rahane. Lyon is yet to get a wicket but he has created quite a few chances already. The Aussies were sharp on the field and it was evident with the wicket of Vihari when Josh Hazlewood nailed the throw at the non-striker's end. However, once Pant arrived, the Aussies looked a bit out of sorts against him as he took the attack to the opposition and have given a few things to ponder for the Aussies in this Lunch break.

India started cautiously at the start with Pujara and Rahane blocking and defending well but Rahane fell when he was starting to show some aggression. Pujara was in his own zone as he kept blocking everything thrown at him. He was troubled a bit by Lyon but he started to attack him after facing 100 balls. Vihari didn't look too confident and his innings was cut short when he tried to sneak a single and Hazlewood inflicted a terrific run out. Pant then came out with a positive mindset and hit a few boundaries. He along with Pujara made sure India didn't lose another wicket in the session.

An excellent session of play! One would assume with the two big wickets, the Aussies will take the session. India have scored 84 runs in the session though and the deficit now is 158. The Aussies looked all over the Indians as they put a lot of pressure on Pujara and struck a couple of big blows but Pant's arrival has changed things a tad bit. The southpaw is not missing out on the scoring opportunities.
A short ball on middle and leg, Pant easily sits under it. With that it's LUNCH ON DAY 3.
Good length ball outside off, Pant lets it go through to Paine.
Length on off, Pant defends this one towards gully.
A shortish ball just around off, Pant leaves that one. The ball however passes very close to his helmet.
Again a length ball outside off, Pant is not interested in playing that.
Length ball outside off, Pant shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, left alone by Pujara.
Another single as Pant works this short ball on the leg side.
Short and just outside off, punched to the left of the cover fielder for one.
Full and on middle, it is pushed down to long on for one.
Tossed up and around off, kept out.
Shortish and down the leg side. Left alone by Pant.
Good running this by Pant. A length ball on off, Pant softly plays it towards covers and calls his partner for a quick run to keep strike.
A length around off, Pant plays it straight to point.
Length around off, Pant pushes it on the off side.
Bouncer now on middle, Pant ducks under this one.
Length around middle and leg, Pant looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Appeal from the bowler but the umpire is unmoved. The ball was pitching outside leg as shown by the replays.
Green starts with a length ball outside off, Pant lets it go through to Paine.
Bowling change. Cameron Green is on now.
This is again outside off, Pujara is not interested.
This one is fired outside off, it turns away as Pujara lets it be. Paine cannot stop it but Smith at first slip does well to stop the ball to his left.
Pant tucks it through mid-wicket now and takes one.
Full and outside off, Pujara hits it hard to the right of the cover fielder. A half stop and they take a single.
Friendly full toss, pushed down to long on for one.
Short ball around off, Pant pulls it hard but the ball hits the short leg fielder.
Shortish around middle, Pant hops and tucks this one past the short leg fielder towards deep square for a single. It was really close to the fielder there at short leg. A run taken in the end.
Another bumper around off, Pant leaves that alone.
A perfect response from Starc now. A bouncer on middle and leg, Pant sways away from it.
FOUR! CUTS AND CUTS HARD! A short ball outside off, Pant hops and cuts this fiercely towards third man for a boundary. Pant looking good here.
Length around off, pushed towards point.
Length ball around off, Pant defends this one towards covers.
Full and wide outside off, Pujara nails the drive but finds the cover fielder.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, kept out.
On middle, clipped towards short fine leg for one.

FOUR! Pant goes after Labuschagne straightaway. A tossed up ball coming into Pant, he sits down and slogs this one towards deep mid-wicket to collect a boundary. Pant will not let the part time spinner settle down here.

NOT OUT! There is nothing on Hot Spot and nothing on Snicko either. A rank long hop down the leg side. Pant goes for the pull but misses. Paine moves to his right and catches it. He appeals but not out says the umpire. Paine has a word with the bowler and then he goes for the review. Replays roll in and it confirms that the onfield call is a correct one. Australia lose another review.

And Paine thinks his plan has worked. Pant has been given not out for a catch down the leg side. Paine thinks there is some bat and he has gone for the review. There's nothing on Hot Spot and Snicko shows clear gap between glove and ball. Pant survives.
Marnus Labuschagne is on now. Maybe a plan from the Aussies to lure Pant in playing some big shots.
Good length and around off, Pujara is on his toes to block.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Lovely bouncer from Starc. It is on middle and leg, Pant takes his eyes off and looks to fend it off. The ball takes the gloves and lobs up. It goes down to fine leg for one.
LEG BYE! A shortish ball on the body, drifting down leg, Pujara tries to sway away from that but the ball hits the elbow guard and goes towards fine leg. The batsmen cross over for a leg bye.
Shortish on the body, Pant tucks this one towards fine leg for a run.
Fuller length outside off, Pant drives this one in the gap at cover-point and comes back for a couple before the fielder there returns the ball.
FOUR! Super shot from Pujara. Short and just outside off, Pujara rocks back and punches it through covers. It races away to the fence. Pujara on 40 now.
Short and wide outside off, slapped to deep point for one.
Fired outside off, left alone.
Looped on middle, played back to Lyon.
Fuller around off, Pant defends this one on the off side.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller this time outside off, Pujara is not interested in playing the drive there. Left alone.
Length around off, Pujara pushes this one to point.
Length and outside off, Pujara lets it go through to Paine.
Fuller this time around middle, kept out by Pujara.
Shortish around middle, Pujara tucks this away towards square leg.
Back of a length on off, Pujara is solid in his defense here.
Floated outside off, pushed towards cover. 7 off the over.
Pujara rotates strike as his jumps out of his crease and flicks it wide of the man at mid on. A diving stop there but a single is taken.
Smartly pushes the next fuller one towards covers for a single.

FOUR! That's how Pant plays. He is not going to just keep blocking and blocking. Just a fraction short and a bit of room too. Pant slams it through point and it races away to the fence. 150 up for the Indians.
Flat and just outside off, punched towards cover for a single.
Fired it fuller and outside off, Pujara pads it away.
Good response from Pant. Shortish and just around off, Pant punches it through covers and bags a brace.
Sharp bouncer around off, Pant sways away from the line. Starc has an advice or two for Pant there.
Length ball around off, punched towards mid off.
Short and around off, poked towards point.
Pant is underway! Good length and just around off, Pant opens the bat face and guides it wide of backward point. Two taken.
A full toss around off to begin, Pant punches it towards mid on.
Mithell Starc is back on. 10-5-25-0 from him so far.
Looped up and around off, played back to the bowler again. End of a successful over for Australia.
Flatter and around off, punched back to Lyon.
On middle, punched down the ground.
Tossed up around off, Pujara comes down the track and pads this one away on the off side.
Rishabh Pant walks in at number 6 now.

OUT! RUN OUT! Vihari is short. Stunning work from Hazlewood. A fuller ball just outside off, Vihari jumps out of his crease and pushes it wide of the man at mid off. He calls for the single straightaway and Pujara responds. Hazlewood from mid off dives to his right, stops the ball and hits the stumps at the non-striker's end, did that all in one motion. The Aussies celebrate. The third umpire has been called for and one replay is enough to send Vihari packing. His stay in the middle has been cut short, because of some stunning work from the big Josh.
Direct hit and looks like Vihari is a gonner. The Aussies are celebrating already. And replays show that Vihari is not even in the frame.
Tossed up outside off, Pujara comes down and works this towards mid on for a quick single.
Length ball outside off, pushed towards covers.
Back of a length around off, Vihari defends this one towards short leg.
Bumper now on middle and leg, Vihari ducks under it.
Length ball drifting down leg, clipped towards leg gully. The fielder does well to stop the ball.
Fuller length around off, Vihari defends this out solidly.
Short ball outside off, Vihari lets it be.
He flicks again but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Full and around off, Pujara comes down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket for two more.
Short and around off, punched wide of mid off for a single.
Tossed up outside off, tucked towards short leg.
Around off, Vihari blocks this out on the on side.
Tossed up around off, pushed towards mid on.
A length ball on the pads, Pujara tries to flick but misses. A bit of appeal from Paine but nothing from the umpire.
On the pads, Pujara looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad.
Back of a length and around middle, tucked towards the leg side.
Gets back to blocking the ball. It is once again full and on middle, Pujara bocks it back to Josh.
FOUR! SHOT! Another boundary for Pujara. He is turning things around here. A fullish ball around off, Pujara punches it down the ground and it races away to the fence.
Fuller and around off, blocked.
Loopy and around off, Vihari this time comes on the front foot and blocks.

Chance again! Around off, Vihari looks to defend on the leg side, gets an inside edge on his pads and the ball lobs over Wade at short leg. He jumps and tries to take that but couldn't take it. 2nd chance gone down at short leg this morning.
On off, defended on the leg side.
Floated around middle and leg, Vihari flicks this one fine towards fine leg area and comes back for a couple.
Floated around off, Vihari works this on the leg side.
Tossed up around off, played straight back to Lyon.

DRINKS! A fine phase of play. Rahane started well but fell to Cummins as he dragged one onto his stumps. Pujara has looked solid in his defense against the pacers. Lyon has troubled him a bit but he decided to take him on and hit him for a couple of boundaries in his last over. These two are having a good battle out in the middle. Another interesting phase coming up.
Fullish around middle, Pujara blocks this out. 3rd consecutive maiden from Hazlewood.
Fullish around middle, Pujara turns this one towards mid-wicket.
Short but down the leg, Pujara gets away from the line and lets it go through to Paine.
Length on middle, clipped towards square leg for no run.
Fuller length again on middle, Pujara defends this one solidly.
Fuller on middle, Pujara watches and blocks this out.
Full and around off, flicked to mid on for nothing. 11 off the over. A good one for the Indians.
Looped up and around off, kept out.

Three now! Excellent running. Floated outside off, Pujara flicks it through square leg. They take two but Pujara wants three. Vihari is slow in taking off for the thrid one but the throw from Starc isn't that great. So, they make it easiy in the end. Excellent from Pujara in this over.
FOUR! Slapped away! More aggression. Lyon drops it short and gives enough room for Pujara to slam it through the cover region for another boundary. He is putting pressure here on Lyon.
On off, Pujara defends it.

FOUR! Signs of aggression from Pujara. A fuller ball around off, Pujara dances down the track and nails the drive through mid on. The fielder gives it a chase, dives but fails to cut it off. First boundary for Pujara and it comes on the 101st ball of his innings.
Fuller around off, pushed towards covers. Vihari looks for a single but Pujara says a loud 'NO'. Another maiden from Hazlewood.
In the channel outside off, shouldered arms by Vihari.
A bumper now around off, Vihari sits under this one.
Length on middle, turned away towards short leg.
Length around middle, Vihari flicks this one towards square leg. The fielder dives to his right and stops the single.
Fullish around off, Vihari lets this one go through to Paine. A hint of reverse as the ball passes the stumps.

Dropped? Not sure. Tossed up and outside off, Pujara comes down the track and looks to play but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball lobs wide of the man at silly point who tries to catch but misses.
Vihari is off the mark. Fuller and around off, pushed towards cover for a single.
Looped up on middle, turning in. Vihari lets it be.
Loopy and just around off, defended.
Fuller and around off, bunted on the leg side.
Flatter and around off, pushed to mid on off the back foot.
Fuller around off, pushed towards point. Good probing over this by Hazlewood.
Short again on the body, Pujara sits under it.
Fullish length on middle, Pujara watches it closely and blocks it out.
Short ball on the body, Pujara ducks under this one.
Fullish around middle and leg, Pujara flicks this one towards deep square leg for a brace before the fine leg fielder throws it back to the keeper.
Length ball around off, Pujara just defends it back towards the bowler.
On middle and leg, tucked towards short fine leg.
Fullish around off, worked away towards mid-wicket.
Floated around off, turned away towards short leg.
On off, Vihari plays it on the on side.
Floated around middle and leg, Vihari turns this one towards square leg.
Tossed up outside off, played back to Lyon.
Maiden over from Hazlewood. Finishes the over with a bouncer, Pujara sways and ducks under it.
Length ball outside off, comes back in a little, left alone by Pujara.
Similar ball around off, Pujara is solid in his front foot defense.
Fullish around off, Pujara comes forward and defends this one on the pitch.
In the channel outside off, Pujara is happy leaving that one.
Here's Josh Hazlewood with the ball.
Hazlewood starts with a length ball on middle, Pujara defends it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, poked towards short third man for one. End of a probing over from Lyon.
Flat and around off, pushed to the right of the bowler.
Flatter and around middle, turned towards square leg.

NOT OUT! Nothing on Hot Spot and Snicko. Pujara survives. Lyon floats it fullish and on middle and leg, Pujara looks to defend but it spins in. The ball lobs towards short leg after hitting the pad. Flatter and around off, punched towards mid off for nothing. 4 off the first over of Day 3.
Another single! Shortish and just outside off, it is cut wide of the man at gully. 100 up for the Indians.
Floats this one around off, Pujara keeps it out.
Pujara is underway too! A flatter ball around off, Pujara goes back and punches it through covers for a brace.

We are ready to begin! The Australian players have made their way out to the middle and the Indian overnight batters follow them to resume their innings. Australia will begin with spin. Interesting from Paine. Here's Nathan Lyon. Rahane to face. Here we go...

Pitch report - Glenn McGrath observes the 22-yard from the studio. He tells that by the look of the wicket, it looks like there is plenty of runs on offer. Tells that the pitch looks on the slower side, in spite of the tinge of green grass. Mentions that there are some footmarks outside the off stump of right-handers. Adds that we might see an uneven bounce as well on a few deliveries.

Hello and welcome to one and all! It is almost time for Day 3 of the 3rd Test between Australia and India. After an engrossing Day 2, where India managed to keep their noses slightly ahead, courtesy, brilliant bowling in the first 2 sessions and then in the final session, the Indian openers added 50-plus before falling. With Ajinkya Rahane and Cheteshwar Pujara out in the middle and the pitch not offering much to the bowlers, one would believe that these two will make most of the good batting conditions and take India to a big first inning score, something which Australia failed to do after having a decent score after the first hour of Day 2. However, their bowlers will look to strike early in the morning session to put the Indians under pressure early on. We will find out how things pan out. Welcome again to Day 3 of the coverage. Action coming your way soon.
... DAY 3, SESSION 1 ...

Right then. An even day of cricket by the looks of things, but maybe India are slightly ahead of their counterparts. Australia will hope that they can come back strongly on Day 3 and start the Day picking up a couple of wickets. Whereas, India, will be banking on two of their best red-ball cricketers, Pujara and Rahane to see them through the early nerves and take them to safer shores. Join us on Saturday, 09th January 2021 on 1000 local (2300 GMT, THE PREVIOUS DAY). We hope to have your company for that. Until then, ADIOS AND TAKE CARE!

Steven Smith is up for a quick chat! He starts off by saying that the pitch is a bit up and down and their bowlers will look to keep it stump to stump on Day 3 to let the pitch assist them. He says its always nice playing at the SCG, his home ground and he loves scoring runs in front of his home crowd.

In response to this, India started off solidly courtesy of their new opening duo of Rohit Sharma and Shubman Gill, who stitched a 70-run stand, before Sharma gifted his wicket away. However, Gill kept moving along and also reached his half-century in the process but a wonderful delivery by Cummins made the Australians see the back of him. After that, Pujara and Rahane, possibly the best Indian Test players, safely negotiated proceedings until the end of play for Day 2.

Steven Smith, though, had other plans as even though he kept losing his partners on the other end, he kept motoring on and played really well to reach his 27th Test ton and ended up with 131 runs to his name. His show with the bat along with small cameos from Starc and Marnus early on saw the Aussies end with 338 in their first innings score. Jadeja, again was the man of the moment as he scalped 4 wickets and also effected the run out of Steven Smith, who did not look like he wanted to stop.

In the first session, Smith and Labuschagne continued from where they left off and also added 100 runs to their partnership. That was until Jadeja decided to spin the Australian batters into a web of his own. First, he got rid of Labuschagne, who was on 91 and then also sent Wade back into the hut. Bumrah, towards the end of the first session also took the wicket of Green and India were on top heading into Lunch.

Another great day of cricket comes to a close. Both the teams have looked to battle it out and have given it their all but in the end, one would say that this was more India's day than it was Australia's. They bowled really well in the first two sessions and then showed what they could do with the bat as well and have added 96 to their first innings total and have also reduced the lead to 242 runs. Rahane will walk back with a smile wider than that of Paine's at the end of Day 2.
